      • setAcl

        public Acl setAcl(String repositoryId,
         String objectId,
         Acl aces)
        Description copied from interface: ExtendedAclService
        Removes the direct ACEs of an object and sets the provided ACEs. The changes are local to the given object and are not propagated to dependent objects. The effect of this operation depends on the repository and the binding. It is recommended to process the returned ACL after the method has been called and check if result matches the expectation.
        Specified by:
        setAcl in interface ExtendedAclService
        Parameters:
        repositoryId - the identifier for the repository
        objectId - the identifier for the object
        aces - the ACEs
        Returns:
        the ACL of the object
